Introduction

Music taste is deeply personal and can be traced back to many aspects of a persons life. It is deeply intertwined with both internal and external processes a person goes through. It can be considered a mysterious, even mystical, topic. Nevertheless, it has been a topic that researchers have been trying to demystify and generate theories about. Previous research has shown that there is a consistent relationship between personality and musical preference (Dunn et al., 2011). Personality has proven to be a key in understanding the structure of music preference. The correlations that have been found inspired us to set up our own research to investigate this relationship. In our research, we have tried to answer the question What is the influence of someones personality on their music taste?.

Motivation

Previous investigations on the relation between music taste and personality were largely based on self-developed models of musical preference (Dunn et al., 2011). These models mainly relied on individuals self-reports to measure and define their musical preference, meaning that they were based on subjective models. Objective tools such as the Spotify API were rarely used. We expect our research to contribute new insights, because the methods we have used can be regarded as more objective than previous measurements of musical preference.
